Postman Setup — 4 Requests
Request 1 — Upload the file ✅ Start here
Field	Value
Method	POST
URL	http://localhost:8001/docx/upload
Body tab	form-data
Key	file → change type dropdown from Text to File
Value	Browse → select your .docx file
Click Send → copy the job_id from the response:

json
{
  "job_id": "a3f9b2c1-...",
  "status": "queued",
  "message": "'MyReport.docx' queued..."
}
Request 2 — Poll status (repeat until "done")
Field	Value
Method	GET
URL	http://localhost:8001/docx/status/PASTE_JOB_ID_HERE
Keep clicking Send every few seconds. You'll see:

json
{ "status": "processing" }   ← still running
{ "status": "done", "tables_count": 2, "images_count": 3, ... }  ← finished
{ "status": "error", "error": "..." }  ← something went wrong
Request 3 — Download the Markdown
Field	Value
Method	GET
URL	http://localhost:8001/docx/download/PASTE_JOB_ID_HERE/markdown
In Postman click "Save Response → Save to a file" to download MyReport.md

Request 4 — Download the Semantic JSON
Field	Value
Method	GET
URL	http://localhost:8001/docx/download/PASTE_JOB_ID_HERE/semantic
Bonus — Swagger UI (all endpoints in browser)
http://localhost:8001/docs
You can test everything here too without Postman.

